    "This emphasis on languages with abundant resources has created a disparity in hate speech research, especially for languages with fewer resources, such as Irish, Portuguese, Norwegian, and various South Asian languages [5].",
    "Machine learning-based methodsH.",
    "Elzayady et al. [18] introduced a method for detecting HS in Arabic dialects using a combination of classical machine learning (ML) and DL-based approaches in two phases, incorporating personality traits.",
    "In the first phase, the AraPersonality dataset was used, applying correlation validation between personality traits and HS.",
    "In the second phase, the Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency (TF-IDF) was used for feature extraction."
